title_ssi: Aeromagnetic map of Minnesota, central region, Plate 1
description_ts: Total magnetic intensity anomaly (relative to the earth's magnetic field), color coded, scale 1:250,000.  Interpretation of magnetic data collected from airborne surveys, the map colors indicate the distribution and concentration of magnetic minerals (primarily iron-bearing) within the upper crust of the earth. Electronic file available at: ftp://mgssun6.mngs.umn.edu/map_catalog/pdf/umn21100.pdf
contact_information_ssi: Minnesota Geological Survey, 2642 University Avenue, St. Paul, MN 55114
rights_ssi: Public domain.  We request that if the images are used credit be given to the Minnesota Geological Survey, University of Minnesota.
